  "text": "BLER range and the minimum SNR value are required for estimating CQI values for each user. This file is also loaded into memory to be used by the receivers HsdpaPhy object to determine whether an ACK or NACK should be generated for the received SNR [CITATION_1] . The scheduling strategy has significant impact on the performance of the mac-hs flow control, as the amount of transferred data is dependent on its resource allocation. The scheduling is done at the BS (Mac/Hsdpa). The algorithm in general followed for scheduling is given below: S1: The BS initially receives the packet from RLC by using Sendown function. S2: For each packet the flow id and priority are considered and the index value is calculated using the formula S7: After this, the updation of HARQ process is done depending on receiving ACK/NACK. S8: Finally the mac-hs PDUs will be assigned to the users correctly by the HARQ process. S9: Repeat the steps from S5-S8 for every HARQ process.",
